# Objects ğŸ—‚ï¸

Key-value pairs to represent entities.

```javascript
const car = {
  brand: "Tesla",
  model: "Model 3",
  year: 2023,
  start: function() {
    console.log("Vroom!");
  }
};

console.log(car.brand); // Dot notation
console.log(car["model"]); // Bracket notation
car.start();
```

# High-Order Methods ğŸ› ï¸

Modern ways to loop and transform arrays.

```javascript
const nums = [1, 2, 3];

// forEach: Loop
nums.forEach(n => console.log(n));

// map: Transform (creates new array)
const doubled = nums.map(n => n * 2); // [2, 4, 6]

// filter: Select subset
const big = nums.filter(n => n > 1); // [2, 3]
```
